  "text": "NPN classification has many applications in logic synthesis [CITATION_1] - [CITATION_2] and technology mapping [CITATION_3] - [CITATION_4] for FPGAs. In synthesis, optimal or near-optimal circuits for a large number of practical functions can be precomputed and stored in a library. With Boolean function classification, only one function in each equivalence class needs to be in the library, resulting in a dramatic reduction of the library size [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
